==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Maundy Thursday
<hw>Maun"dy Thurs"day</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[OE. <ets>maunde</ets> a
command, OF. <ets>mand⟦eacute⟧</ets>, L. <ets>mandatum</ets>, from
<ets>mandare</ets> to command. See called from the ancient custom of
washing the feet of the poor on this day, which was taken to be the
fulfillment of the ⟦ldquo⟧new commandment,⟦rdquo⟧ <au>John xiii. 5,
34.</au>]</ety> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>The Thursday in Passion week, or
next before Good Friday.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maungy</ent>⟦br⟧
